es to have a baby with Teddy. Vanessa returns when Liam's movie emerges a hit and tells him she is legally still his manager, forcing them to keep working together (and so she can continue to pilfer from his salary). Also, Dixon calls Adrianna to give their relationship a second chance. Adrianna agrees, but soon regrets it when Dixon fails to show up at their meeting spot leading her to believe that he bailed on her again as she leaves for Las Vegas with Austin. While on a phone call to Navid, Dixon's car is hit by a truck, leaving his condition unknown. |LineColor = DC7B70 }} }}</onlyinclude>
== Production == [[File:90210season4.png|right|upright|thumb|400px|Promotional marketing campaign for the fourth season.]] On {{nowrap|March 17, 2011}}, TV Line announced that [[Rebecca Rand Kirshner|Rebecca Sinclair]] would not renew her contract as executive producer for season four.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/03/90210-showrunner-rebecca-sinclair-leaving/|title=Exclusive: 90210 Showrunner Steps Down|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=March 17, 2011|work=TV Line|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}</ref> On {{nowrap|April 26, 2011}}, [[The CW]] officially renewed ''90210'' for a fourth season.<ref name="Early renewals The CW 2011-12">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/04/26/%E2%80%9Cthe-vampire-diaries%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9Cgossip-girl%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9C90210%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9Csupernatural%E2%80%9D-americas-next-top-model-renewed-by-the-cw/90700/comment-page-4#comment-819642|title="The Vampire Diaries," "Gossip Girl," "90210," "Supernatural" & "America's Next Top Model" Renewed By The CW|last=Gorman|first=Bill|date=April 26, 2011|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}</ref> On {{nowrap|May 12, 2011}}, it was announced that former ''[[Life Unexpected]]'' executive producers Patti Carr and Lara Olsen had been hired to take over the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/05/12/90210-life-unexpected-showrunners/|title='90210' hires 'Life Unexpected' showrunners|last=Ram|first=Archana|date=May 12, 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=May 24, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110525095054/http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/05/12/90210-life-unexpected-showrunners/| archivedate= May 25, 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> Their production credits also include ''[[Private Practice (TV series)|Private Practice]]''.<ref name="CW schedule"/>
On {{nowrap|May 19, 2011}}, with the reveal of The CW's 2011–12 schedule, it was announced the series would be returning to Tuesday at {{nowrap|8:00&nbsp;pm}} Eastern/{{nowrap|7:00&nbsp;pm}} Central as a lead-in to new [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]] series, ''[[Ringer (TV series)|Ringer]]''.<ref name="schedule">{{cite web|author=Matt Webb Mitovich |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/05/fall-tv-preview-cw-schedule/ |title=The CW's Fall Schedule: Sarah Michelle Gellar Back on Tuesdays, Nikita Makes Move |publisher=TVLine.com |date=May 19, 2011 |accessdate=May 24, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110608142922/http://www.tvline.com/2011/05/fall-tv-preview-cw-schedule/| archivedate= June 8, 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> The fourth season premiered on Tuesday, {{nowrap|September 13, 2011}}.<ref name="CW 2011 premiere dates">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/06/20/the-cw-network-announces-fall-2011-premiere-dates/96084/|title=The CW Network Announces Fall 2011 Premiere Dates|last=Seidman|first=Robert|date=June 20, 2011|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=June 20, 2011}}</ref> On August 3, 2011, The CW ordered two additional episodes for the fourth season, which will now total at 24.<ref name="extra episodes">{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/08/cw-orders-additional-episodes-of-four-returning-dramas/|title=CW Orders Additional Episodes Of Four Returning Dramas|last=Andreeva |first= Nellie|date=August 3, 2011|work=Deadline|accessdate=August 3, 2011}}</ref>
A "[[Rock the Vote]]" themed episode aired in October, where [[Cobra Starship]] performed their new single "#1Nite."<ref name="Rock the Vote">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/08/22/90210-cobra-starship-to-guest/|title=Cobra Starship to rock out on '90210' – EXCLUSIVE|last=Gonzalez|first=Sandra|date=August 22, 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=August 23, 2011}}</ref> Episode 8 was in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]].<ref name="AA Las Vegas">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/09/ask-ausiello-spoilers-on-glee-greys-anatomy-community/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Glee, Grey's Anatomy, Community, Gossip Girl, HIMYM and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=September 6, 2011|work=TV Line|accessdate=September 12, 2011}}</ref> [[All American Rejects]] performed in the fifteenth episode of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aoltv.com/2011/12/05/exclusive-90210-all-american-rejects/|title=EXCLUSIVE: See Who's Rocking '90210' Next|last=Furlong|first=Maggie|date=December 5, 2011|work=[[AOL TV]]|accessdate=December 5, 2011}}</ref>
The CW originally announced as the series would return from its mid-season hiatus with new episodes on January 10, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/11/02/the-cw-announces-2012-midseason-schedule/109422/|title=The CW Announces 2012 Midseason Schedule|last=Seidman|first=Robert|date=November 2, 2011|work=TVbytheNumbers|accessdate=December 13, 2011}}</ref> However, The CW later announced ''90210'' would return on January 17 to lead into the series premiere of new reality series, "[[Remodeled (TV series)|Remodeled]]".<ref name="revised CW">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/12/09/pr-5/113291/|title="Remodeled" To Get Multiple Runs During Its First Two Weeks On The CW; Delays '90210,' 'Ringer' Returns|last=Gorman|first=Bill|date=December 9, 2011|work=TVbytheNumbers|accessdate=December 13, 2011}}</ref> American rock band, [[Train (band)|Train]], appeared in an episode which aired in February 2012. The band performed their latest single "Drive By" in their cameo appearance. The same episode saw the characters going to a music festival in the desert.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/01/09/train-90210/|title=Train to make musical stop on '90210' – EXCLUSIVE|last=Gonzalez|first=Sandra|date=January 9, 2012|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=January 23, 2012}}</ref>
=== Cast and characters === Before the end of the third season, it was announced that [[Lori Loughlin]] and [[Ryan Eggold]] would not be returning to the series' fourth season.<ref name="Loughlin, Eggold">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/01/90210-exclusive-lori-loughlin-ryan-eggold-to-exit/|title=90210 Exclusive: Lori Loughlin, Ryan Eggold Exit|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=January 26, 2011|work=TV Line|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}</ref> However, Loughlin has already been asked to return for "some episodes," by the former CW president, if her schedule permits it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/s114/90210/news/a304315/90210-star-its-right-time-to-leave.html|title='90210' star: 'It's right time to leave'|last=Wightman|first=Catriona|date=February 17, 2011|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}</ref> [[The CW]] press release for their 2011–12 season, included all cast members [[Shenae Grimes]], [[Tristan Wilds]], [[AnnaLynne McCord]], [[Jessica Stroup]], [[Michael Steger]], [[Jessica Lowndes]], [[Matt Lanter]], [[Trevor Donovan]] and [[Gillian Zinser]].<ref name="CW schedule">{{cite web|url=http://blog.cwtv.com/2011/05/19/the-cw-announces-2011-2012-schedule/ |title=THE CW ANNOUNCES 2011–2012 SCHEDULE |date=May 19, 2011 |accessdate=May 24, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110529093919/http://blog.cwtv.com/2011/05/19/the-cw-announces-2011-2012-schedule/ |archivedate=May 29, 2011 }}</ref> AnnaLynne McCord confirmed in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' that the cast would be cut down by the new showrunners, though McCord was assured she would be back.<ref name="McCord confirmed">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/05/17/90210-finale-naomi-pregnant/|title='90210' finale: Scoop on the shocking cliffhanger!|last=Ram|first=Archana|date=May 17, 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=May 24, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110525052703/http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/05/17/90210-finale-naomi-pregnant/| archivedate= May 25, 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> [[Trevor Donovan]] was the first cast member to be dropped as a series regular for the fourth season, although, he will return as a guest star for five episodes in the Fall.<ref name="Trevor Donovan out">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/06/90210-exclusive-trevor-donovan-poised-to-exit/|title=90210 Exclusive: Trevor Donovan Poised to Exit|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|work=TV Line|date=June 6, 2011}}</ref> [[Manish Dayal]] will be returning to the series in a recurring role as Ivy's dying husband, Raj.<ref name="Ivy and Raj back for season 4">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/06/ask-ausiello-spoilers-on-true-blood-supernatural-how-i-met-your-mother-bones-and-more/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on True Blood, Bones, Supernatural, Mother, Castle and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=June 7, 2011|work=TVLine|accessdate=June 8, 2011}}</ref> Donovan will be the only series regular dropped from the series. Five new recurring characters will be introduced in the Fall. Austin, described as a charming and hunky cowboy and the son of a country music superstar. Holly, Naomi's rival at California University. Jeremy, a student at CU who forges an immediate connection with Annie, but may have an ulterior motive. Jane, a young widow and love-interest for Liam, and Leila, Navid's younger and trouble making sister.<ref name="AA 90210">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/06/ask-ausiello-spoilers-on-castle-true-blood-glee-dexter-90210-and-more/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Castle, True Blood, Glee, Dexter, 90210 and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=June 14, 2011|work=TVLine|accessdate=June 15, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110615103956/http://www.tvline.com/2011/06/ask-ausiello-spoilers-on-castle-true-blood-glee-dexter-90210-and-more/| archivedate= June 15, 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> Producers are also looking to cast Navid's uncle, ''Amal'' who was also his fathers business partner. He is described as charming on the surface, but a bad guy and somebody "you don't want to mess with."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/uberblog/watch_with_kristin/b248356_spoiler_chat_get_summer_tv_scoop_on.html|title=Spoiler Chat: Get Summer TV Scoop on Weeds, True Blood and More!|date=June 20, 2011|work=Watch With Krisin (E! Online)|accessdate=June 21, 2011}}</ref> [[Kristina Apgar]], [[Megalyn Echikunwoke]] and [[Justin Deeley]] were later cast as Jane, Holly and Austin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/90210-privileged-star-books-recurring-208010|title='90210': 'Privileged' Star Books Recurring Role (Exclusive)|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=July 5, 2011|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=July 6, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/90210-justin-deeley-megalyn-echikunwoke/|title=90210 Exclusive: Newcomer Justin Deeley Joins Season 4 Cast as… Brad Pitt?!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=July 6, 2011|work=TV Line|accessdate=July 16, 2011}}</ref> [[Stephen Amell]] also reported that he signed to appear on the show for at least two or more episodes playing Jim Conrad who will get involved with Liam's life. [[Josh Zuckerman (actor)|Josh Zuckerman]] will return as Naomi's boyfriend, Max, for a handful of episodes.<ref name="Ask Ausiello">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/ask-ausiello-spoilers-castle-fringe-csi-ny-greys/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Castle, Fringe, CSI: NY, Grey's, 90210, Nikita and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=July 12, 2011|work=TV Line|accessdate=July 16, 2011}}</ref> [[Cameron Goodman]] also secured a recurring spot role, playing Bree a college student who convince Annie to work as a professional escort. [[Entertainment Weekly|EW]] has reported that Brooklyn-based rapper, [[Theophilus London]], will make a guest appearance while performing at Naomi's College Kick-Off party in her new mansion, in the season premiere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/07/11/theophilus-london-90210/|title=Theophilus London to perform on '90210' – EXCLUSIVE|last=Rice|first=Lynette|date=July 11, 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=July 16, 2011}}</ref> [[Drew Seeley]] was cast in the series, but was later replaced by ''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]'' actor [[Matt Cohen (actor)|Matt Cohen]] in the role of Jeremy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/07/90210-supernaturals-matt-cohen-replaces-drew-seeley-as-jeremy.html|title='90210': 'Supernatural's' Matt Cohen replaces Drew Seeley as Jeremy|last=MacKenzie|first=Carina|date=July 14, 2011|work=Zap2It|accessdate=July 16, 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68b6Ir6zM?url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/07/90210-supernaturals-matt-cohen-replaces-drew-seeley-as-jeremy.html|archivedate=June 21, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Freddie Smith]] will not return as Teddy's boyfriend, Marco, as their relationship ended over the summer.<ref name="90210 interview new showrunners">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/90210-Season4-Spoilers-CW-Teddy-Adrianna-1035410.aspx|title=90210 Season 4 Spoilers! Is Teddy Gone? Can Adrianna Be Redeemed? Will Naomi Have a Baby?|last=Martin|first=Denise|date=July 17, 2011|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=July 19, 2011}}</ref> Former ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'' star, [[Sarah Hagan]], will play Alana, a member of the sorority Naomi joined in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/08/exclusive-90210-snags-buffy-alum-sarah-hagan/|title=Exclusive: 90210 Snags Buffy Alum Sarah Hagan|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=August 3, 2011|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}</ref> R&B singer, [[Brandy Norwood]] will have a major arc in the fourth season. Her character Marissa Harris-Young,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cwtv.com/shows/90210/episodes|title=90210 – Party Politics