0210-scoop-welcome-back-jen-you-selfish-little/|title='90210' scoop: Welcome back, Jen (you selfish little...)|date=November 9, 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=December 5, 2011}}</ref> [[Nick Zano]] was also cast as Preston Hillingsbrook, a playboy with a lot of cash to blow as the heir to his family's fortune. It was revealed that his character will first become friends with Annie, but will also get romantically involved with another woman on the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/casting_scoop_2_broke_girls_star/280509|title=Casting Scoop: 2 Broke Girls Star Heading to 90210 for Some Romance!|last=Bricker|first=Tierney|date=December 13, 2011|work=E! Online|accessdate=January 23, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68bB3xs2R?url=http://www.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/casting_scoop_2_broke_girls_star/280509|archivedate=June 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[La Toya Jackson]] will guest star in an episode which will air in February. Her character is said to be a brilliant and powerful [[music executive]], who ends up forcing Dixon to make a tough decision by making him a great offer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/90210-cw-la-toya-jackson-guest-star-280605|title='90210' Casts La Toya Jackson in Guest Role That Could Change Dixon's Life (Exclusive)|last=Nededog|first=Jethro|date=January 11, 2012|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=January 23, 2012}}</ref> [[Step Up 2]] actor [[Robert Hoffman (actor)|Robert Hoffman]] will guest star Caleb, a student at seminary school studying to become a priest. When Hoffman's character isn't studying he's a laid back surfer, passionate about community service. He won't make his appearance until a March episode. ''[[Pretty Little Liars (TV series)|Pretty Little Liars]]'' cast [[Yani Gellman]] was cast in a multiple guest arc playing the bad boy Diego, the new potential love interest of Ivy Sullivan. [[American Idol]] season 10 runner-up, [[Haley Reinhart]], will guest star as herself. Reinhart will appear in the March 27 episode, performing at a showcase. She will also sing the first single off her debut album during her appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2012/02/haley-reinhart-american-idol-90210/|title= American Idol Fave Haley Reinhart to Perform on 90210 and Cause Problems for [Spoiler]!)|last=Mitovich|first=Matt|date= February 28, 2012|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=February 28, 2012}}</ref>
