=== Storylines === The fourth season will follow the group after high school. Some will head to college, while some will begin their careers, while all trying to maintain their friendships and create new ones.<ref name="CW schedule"/> Matt Lanter said of the transition to college, "There's real world possibilities that open up when you go to college now, so I'm really looking forward to the stories that they come up with and how they can be exciting in a real life way rather than just walking down the school hallways."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/uberblog/b247060_Spoiler_Chat__Which__i_True_Blood__i__Lead_Goes_Vigilante_in_Season_Four_.html|title=Spoiler Chat: Which True Blood Lead Goes Vigilante in Season Four?|date=June 13, 2011|work=E! Online (WWK)|accessdate=June 15, 2011}}</ref> It was announced that a major male character will develop a drug habit.<ref name="Ask Ausiello"/> Later revealed to be Dixon. It has also been revealed that only one series regular will be attending college full-time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/ask-ausiello-spoilers-bones-ncis-dexter/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Private Practice, NCIS, True Blood, Parenthood, Tree Hill, and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=July 19, 2011|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=July 20, 2011}}</ref> Executive producer Patti Carr revealed that Naomi will buy an over-the-top mansion that she'll turn into a sorority house where friends such as Annie, Silver and newlyweds Ivy and Raj will live. It has also been revealed that Dixon won't be going to college, he will instead pursue a music career.<ref name="TV GUIDE">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Kecks-Exclusives-90210-1036529.aspx|title=Keck's Exclusives: 90210 First Look|date=August 12, 2011|last=Keck|first=William|accessdate=August 23, 2011}}</ref> In the "Rock the Vote" themed episode, Naomi will throw a lavish registration party at her mansion.<ref name="Rock the Vote"/> Navid and Silver will be forced to act as parents and look after Navid's sister, who decides to stay in L.A. when her family moves to Switzerland. Navid will also hire Silver to work for him, so they can spend more time together.<ref name="E! Online">{{cite web|title=90210's Michael Steger Reveals "Huge Twist" in New Season Read more:|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/90210s_michael_steger_reveals_huge/260130?dlvrit=51396|publisher=Jenna Mullins|accessdate=August 26, 2011}}</ref>
[[Kristin Dos Santos]] reported that Annie will begin a new profession after Marla's family contest the will left to her.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/spoiler_chat_chuck_bass_attacked_by/256906?dlvrit=51396|title=Spoiler Chat: Chuck Bass Attacked by a Werewolf?! Get Scoop on Gossip Girl, House, Glee and More|last=Santos|first=Kristin|date=August 8, 2011|work=E! Online|accessdate=August 29, 2011}}</ref> Michael Ausiello later reported that she will become a professional escort.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/08/ask-ausiello-spoilers-gossip-girl-glee-90210/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Gossip Girl, 90210, Glee, Sons of Anarchy, Housewives and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=August 23, 2011|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=August 29, 2011}}</ref> Liam will become a male model this season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/08/ask-ausiello-greys-how-i-met-your-mother-community/|title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on Grey's Anatomy, HIMYM, Community, Gossip Girl, Glee and More!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=August 30, 2011|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=September 5, 2011}}</ref> Teddy will get "married" (Same-sex marriage is not recognized in Nevada.) to his boyfriend, Shane in the Las Vegas episode, scheduled to air in early November.<ref name="Teddy, married">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Kecks-Exclusives-Look-1038344.aspx|title=Keck's Exclusives: First Look at 90210's Teddy Getting Married|last=Keck|first=William|date=October 2, 2011|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=October 4, 2011}}</ref> Adrianna will reignite her musical dreams, and attempt to get her baby back.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/10/90210-jessica-lowndes-season-4-preview/|title=90210's Jessica Lowndes Previews Adrianna's Redemption (and Surprise Musical Comeback!)|last=Masters|first=Megan|date=October 18, 2011|work=[[TV Line]]|accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref> Matt Lanter revealed in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' that the fall finale will end with a life or death situation with Liam. He said, "We're not really sure what happens to him or if he returns, how he returns."<ref name="Matt Lanter EW"/> [[Entertainment Weekly|EW]] confirmed that Jen Clark will return for three episodes. Her debut will begin with a visit at the end of episode 16, with baby Jacques in tow. Jen coerces Naomi into helping her find a rich, eligible bachelor, but the guy ends up having eyes for Naomi, instead.<ref name="EW.com"/> [[Arielle Kebbel]] who portrays Vanessa, the girl who ran into Liam, told "As the season continues, Liam and Vanessa get closer and learn they have similar troubled pasts." She also added, "I think that brings them closer together. Instead of judging each other's pasts, they see the good in one another and encourage change for the future."<ref name="Kebbel" />
At the end of the mid-season premiere, Silver discovered that the man she has been dating is also the man who adopted Adrianna's baby.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Should Old Acquaintance Be Forgot?|series=90210|credits=Jenna Lamia (writer) & Cherie Nowlan (director)|network=[[The CW Television Network|The CW]]|airdate=January 17, 2012|season=4|number=13}}</ref>
