{{Featured article}}
[[Category:Ukiyo-e| ]]
[[Category:Arts in Japan]]
[[Category:Schools of Japanese art]]
[[Category:Printmaking]]

{{italic title}} The '''''Yangzhong Puffer Fish,''''' or the "Puffer Fish Tower" is a notable 295-foot long [[bronze]] statue in the shape of the [[puffer fish]]. Weighing 2,300 tons and reportedly costing $11 million, this statue sits on the banks of the [[Yangtze River]] in the [[Jiangsu Province]] of [[China]]. Work on this project was completed in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinanews.com/tp/hd2011/2013/09-27/250054.shtml |title=巨型"河豚"成江苏扬中新地标 造价达7000万元-中新网 |website=Chinanews.com |date= |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/13/world/asia/as-china-vows-austerity-giant-brass-fish-devours-11-million.html?hp&_r=0|title=As China Vows Austerity, Giant Brass Fish Devours $11 Million|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dz.xdkb.net/html/2013-09/27/content_296963.htm |title=现代快报多媒体数字报刊平台 |website=Dz.xdkb.net |date=2013-09-27 |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref>
The ''Yangzhong Puffer Fish'' sculpture is the largest steel-framework sculpture in China, and perhaps the entire world.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jonathan Kaiman |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/sep/27/puffer-fish-statue-state-china-decadence |title=Puffer-fish statue reignites row over state decadence in China &#124; World news |publisher=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2015-12-05}}</ref>
